DATE: 29/1/18
URL: http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/world/10-die-in-egypt-church-attack/520989.html
TITLE:10 die in Egypt church attack.
CONTENT:Ten persons were killed and eight others injured in a terrorist attack on a church in Egypt’s capital today, the government said.

A health ministry spokesman said the attack took place when gunmen on a motorbike opened fire outside Mar Mina church in Helwan area.  At least 10 persons, including eight Coptic Christians, were killed in the shootout outside the south Cairo church, he said, adding, one gunman was shot dead as was a security officer.  The ministry said two of the injured are women, adding it employed 10 ambulances to transfer the injured to hospitals.

State-run MENA news agency reported that the other gunman fled the scene.  There was no immediate claim of responsibility for the attack.  The attack comes days before the Coptic celebration of New Year and orthodox Christmas Day on January 7. — PTI 
